<h3>Bányászsisak</h3>
<p>A Bányászsisak mobil fényforrás, ami 30 másodpercenként 1 tartósságot fogyaszt. <strong>Vas Munkaasztalon</strong> készíthető el a megfelelő Tudáskönyv feloldása után. Akkumulátorral újratölthető.</p>
<div class="tip-card">💡 A fölösleges Tudáskönyveket könyvvé alakíthatod a munkaasztalon, és XP-t kapsz értük.</div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en">
<h2 id="backpacks-en">Backpacks</h2>
<p>Extra inventory space through craftable backpacks with increasing capacity. <strong>B key</strong> = open your equipped backpack!</p>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Backpack</th><th>Slots</th><th>v0.9.0 status</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Leather Backpack</td><td>10</td><td>Starter backpack with a normal recipe</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Big Backpack</td><td>21</td><td>Upgrade the leather backpack with <span class="wiki-item" data-id="big_backpack_upgrade">Big Backpack Upgrade</span></td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(180,120,255,0.12)"><td><strong>Ancient Metal Backpack</strong></td><td><strong>78</strong></td><td><span class="wiki-item" data-id="ancient_metal_backpack_upgrade">Ancient Metal Backpack Upgrade</span> + mercury cauldron + knowledge book</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Copper / Silver / Iron / Gold / Hardstone</td><td>21 / 21 / 36 / 44 / 55</td><td>Legacy backpack tiers still named in the files, but no local v0.9.0 recipe list was found for them</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Mithril / Adamantium</td><td>90 / 102</td><td>Named in the files, but I found no v0.9.0 recipe or upgrade item for actually obtaining them</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="tip-card">🎒 <strong>Reliable v0.9.0 route:</strong> Leather Backpack → Big Backpack Upgrade → Ancient Metal Backpack Upgrade. The last step uses the big backpack upgrade plus 4× Ancient Metal Ingots in a full mercury cauldron with magma/lava heat below for about 30 seconds.</div>

<h2 id="temperature-en">Body Temperature</h2>
<p>Body temperature is optimal at 36–37°C. Fire, lava, and the Nether raise it — water, rain, and ice lower it.</p>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Temperature</th><th>Effect</th></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(100,180,255,0.12)"><td><strong>&lt;35.8°C</strong></td><td>Cold status — slight slowdown</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(100,200,100,0.10)"><td><strong>36–37°C</strong></td><td>✅ Optimal — no debuffs</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,200,0,0.10)"><td><strong>37.2–38.1°C</strong></td><td>Weakness I</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,150,50,0.12)"><td><strong>38.2–39°C</strong></td><td>Weakness I + Fire + Slowness I + 1 HP/min</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,80,30,0.14)"><td><strong>39–45°C+</strong></td><td>Weakness I + Fire + Slowness I + 1 HP/20s</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="warning-box">🔥 <strong>Furnace proximity = overheating!</strong> Standing within 2–3 blocks of a burning furnace can push your body temperature above 37.2°C → <strong>Weakness I</strong>. Solution: stand further away or manage heat with cooling (work near water, hold ice).</div>
<div class="tip-card">🌡️ <strong>Heating modifiers:</strong> Lava (2 blocks near): +0.1°C/35s · Fire (3 blocks): +0.1°C/50s · Holding a torch: +0.1°C/60s · Nether: constant +0.4°C<br>🌡️ <strong>Cooling modifiers:</strong> Submerged in water: −0.1°C/5s · Holding ice: −0.1°C/25s · Eating ice cream: −0.1°C</div>

<h3>Reduced Stack Sizes</h3>
<p>MITE:BE drastically reduces stack sizes for most blocks — requiring serious <strong>inventory and storage planning</strong>!</p>
